  <h2 style="text-align: center">What's New/System Updates</h2>
  <hr />

  <h3>
    Enhanced Reimbursement List Page
    <span style="float: right"> 01/14/2018 </span>
  </h3>
  Users will now be able to search for Reimbursements by Request Id, filter by
  Grant/Sub-Grant, and filter by Status. If more than 40 results are available
  based on the search criteria, results will be paginated. Users also will have
  the ability to Export Results.

  <br /><br />
  <hr />

  <h3>
    Employee line cannot be deleted.
    <span style="float: right"> 06/18/2017 </span>
  </h3>
  Once an employee is added to a budget and the budget is approved, the employee
  line cannot be ‘deleted’.   This will prevent important history of the budget
  from being lost.  The ‘Inactivate’ option should be used when an employee has
  left, been re-assigned or there has been a name change.  Please remember that
  ALL REIMBURSEMENTS containing that employee must be APPROVED prior to being
  ‘Inactivated’.

  <br /><br />
  <hr />

  <h3>
    No longer be able to change a name.
    <span style="float: right"> 06/18/2017 </span>
  </h3>
  When completing a budget modification, you will no longer be able to ‘change a
  name’ in the employee section or a line ‘label’ in the expense section.  Once
  the line has been added and the budget approved, these fields will be locked. 
  This will prevent important history of the budget from being lost.  The
  ‘Inactivate’ option should be used when the line is no longer needed.  Please
  remember that ALL REIMBURSEMENTS containing an amount from the line in
  question must be APPROVED prior to being ‘Inactivated’.

  <br /><br />
  <hr />

  <h3>
    A “FAQ” section can now be found under the Help tab by selecting the ‘Need
    Help?’ button on the upper right side of the screen.
    <span style="float: right"> 04/15/2017 </span>
  </h3>
