  <h3>
    Requesting System Access for Contacts
    <span style="float: right">02/16/2017</span>
  </h3>
  When Contacts are added to the Organization Info tab, they do not
  automatically have access to the system as users. Only CEOs can request that a
  contact be given user access to the system. To do so, the CEO clicks on the
  purple pen under Edit for the contact.
  <br />
  At the bottom of the Edit Contact form, there is a dropdown called User
  Profile. Select the appropriate user profile and click Save and Close.
  <br /><br />
  <strong>User Profile Definitions:</strong>
  <br />
  <strong>Finance Admin –</strong> complete access to all financial information
  and Self-Assessment
  <br />
  <strong>Self-Assessment Only –</strong> access to only the self-assessment, no
  access to financial information
  <br />
  <strong>All Access –</strong> access to all aspects of the system
  <br />
  <strong>Inactive User –</strong> Contact remains inactive (or is moved from an
  active user to inactive) but stays as a contact listed within the organization

  <br /><br />
