  <h3>
    Hourly Rate calculation in Update Budget Form
    <span style="float: right">02/16/2017</span>
  </h3>
  Previously, when entering a salaried employee into the budget, the system
  would calculate the hourly rate using a 2,080 hour work year which is based on
  a 40 hour work week. As some affiliates do not operate using a 40 hour work
  weeks, we have changed this calculation to calculate the hours worked per year
  using figure entered under the "Total Hrs/Wk" field.
  <br /><br /> <strong>Who this will affect:</strong> If your organization does
  not use a 40 hour work week and when filling out your budget you entered a
  number other than "40" for salaried employees under "Total Hrs/Wk", the next
  time you update your budget you will see a change in the calculated "Projected
  Total" column. Many of you with a non-40 hour work week created a work around
  to build your budget to match the actual amount you will charge for each staff
  member, so the next time you update your budget you will be able to replace
  that work around with the true numbers and get the correct "Projected Total"
  <br /><br /> <strong>Who this will NOT affect:</strong> All hourly employees
  and any salaried employees with 40 under "Total Hrs/Wk"

  <br /><br />
  <hr />

  <h3>
    Paid Reimbursements
    <span style="float: right">02/16/2017</span>
  </h3>
  Once a reimbursement request has been been paid, the request will change from
  an "Approved" status to a "Paid" status. The date of the payment will also
  appear next to the status. Additionally, you will be able to see the paid
  status and date in the upper right hand corner when viewing the Reimbursement
  details. You can find the status of all reimbursements under the
  Reimbursements tab.
